.TH GIT-STASH-AUDIT 1 "2026-06-14" "git-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-stash-audit \- inspect and clean git stashes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git stash-audit
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git stash-audit
lists stashes, shows one stash, drops one explicit stash, or drops stashes whose
origin branch can be inferred and no longer exists locally.
.PP
Obsolete classification is intentionally conservative. A stash is considered
obsolete only when its subject identifies an origin branch in Git's normal
.B "On <branch>:"
or
.B "WIP on <branch>:"
format and that local branch no longer exists.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-porcelain
Print stable tab-separated
.B stash
records.
.TP
.BI "\-\-show " index
Show one stash by numeric index.
.TP
.B \-\-patch
Show a patch with
.B \-\-show
instead of a stat summary.
.TP
.BI "\-\-drop " index
Drop one stash by numeric index.
.TP
.B \-\-drop-obsolete
Drop stashes whose inferred local branch is gone. Requires
.B \-\-yes
unless
.B \-\-dry-run
is also used.
.TP
.B \-\-yes
Confirm
.BR \-\-drop-obsolete .
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-dry-run
Print drop actions without changing anything.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Audit or cleanup completed.
.TP
.B 1
Stash operation failed.
.TP
.B 2
Usage or local environment error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-stash (1),
.BR git-repo-state (1)
